## Area 3: `set.cartesian_product(other)` — stub + notes

**File:** `Objects/setobject.c`

### Key structs (`Include/cpython/setobject.h`)

**`setentry`** — lines 20–23:
```c
typedef struct { PyObject *key; Py_hash_t hash; } setentry;
```
Unused: `key == NULL && hash == 0`. Dummy (deleted): `key == dummy` (where `dummy = &_dummy_struct`).

**`PySetObject`** — lines 36–59: fields `fill`, `used`, `mask`, `*table`, `hash` (frozenset only), `finger`, `smalltable[PySet_MINSIZE]`, `*weakreflist`.

### Iteration pattern — `set_next()` lines 709–731

```c
while (i <= mask && (entry->key == NULL || entry->key == dummy)) {
    i++; entry++;
}
```
Call: `set_next((PySetObject *)so, &pos, &entry)` — returns 1 while live entries remain.

### Construction functions

- **`make_new_set(type, iterable)`** — lines 1349–1374; pass `NULL` iterable for empty set
- **`set_add_key(so, key)`** — lines 601–609; calls `_PyObject_HashFast` then `set_add_entry`
- **`set_add_entry(so, key, hash)`** — takes pre-computed hash (use when iterating entries)
- **`make_new_set_basetype(Py_TYPE(so), NULL)`** — used by `set_intersection` (line 1695) to preserve frozenset vs set type

### Template: `set_intersection` — lines 1685–1765

```c
result = make_new_set_basetype(Py_TYPE(so), NULL);
// outer loop: set_next() over one set
// for each entry: set_add_entry(result, key, hash)
return (PyObject *)result;
```

### Thread safety

Single-object ops use `Py_BEGIN_CRITICAL_SECTION(so)` / `Py_END_CRITICAL_SECTION()`.  
Two-object ops use `Py_BEGIN_CRITICAL_SECTION2(so, other)` / `Py_END_CRITICAL_SECTION2()`.  
Clinic-generated wrappers inject these automatically around `*_impl` functions.

### Method tables

**`set_methods[]`** — lines 2784–2807 (has `add`, `discard`, `pop`, etc.)  
**`frozenset_methods[]`** — lines 2897–2911 (separate, read-only: no `add`/`discard`/`pop`)  
`cartesian_product` should appear in **both** tables (it is non-mutating — creates a new frozenset).

### `set_isdisjoint` — copy-paste template

```c
// Clinic input wrapper (clinic/setobject.c.h line 219-232):
// #define SET_ISDISJOINT_METHODDEF \
//     {"isdisjoint", (PyCFunction)set_isdisjoint, METH_O, set_isdisjoint__doc__},
// wrapper applies Py_BEGIN_CRITICAL_SECTION2(so, other)

static PyObject *
set_isdisjoint_impl(PySetObject *so, PyObject *other)
{
    // fast path: both are sets → set_next() loop + set_contains_entry()
    // slow path: PyObject_GetIter(other) + set_contains_key() per item
    Py_RETURN_TRUE; // or Py_RETURN_FALSE
}
```

### Stub

```c
static PyObject *
set_cartesian_product_impl(PySetObject *so, PyObject *other)
{
    PySetObject *result = (PySetObject *)make_new_set(&PyFrozenSet_Type, NULL);
    if (result == NULL) return NULL;

    Py_ssize_t i = 0;
    setentry *entry_a;
    while (set_next(so, &i, &entry_a)) {
        PyObject *a = entry_a->key;
        Py_INCREF(a);

        Py_ssize_t j = 0;
