## Area 6: `list.rotate(n)` — stub + notes

**File:** `Objects/listobject.c`; struct in `Include/cpython/listobject.h`

### `PyListObject` — `Include/cpython/listobject.h` lines 5–22

```c
typedef struct {
    PyObject_VAR_HEAD   /* ob_size = Py_ssize_t, current element count */
    PyObject **ob_item; /* pointer to array of pointers to elements */
    Py_ssize_t allocated;
} PyListObject;
```
Access: `Py_SIZE(self)` for length; `self->ob_item[i]` for elements.

### `list_reverse_impl` — lines 3233–3240

```c
static PyObject *
list_reverse_impl(PyListObject *self)
{
    if (Py_SIZE(self) > 1)
        reverse_slice(self->ob_item, self->ob_item + Py_SIZE(self));
    Py_RETURN_NONE;
}
```

Underlying helper **`reverse_slice`** — lines 1619–1633:
```c
static void
reverse_slice(PyObject **lo, PyObject **hi)
{
    --hi;
    while (lo < hi) {
        PyObject *t = *lo;
        FT_ATOMIC_STORE_PTR_RELEASE(*lo, *hi);
        FT_ATOMIC_STORE_PTR_RELEASE(*hi, t);
        ++lo; --hi;
    }
}
```
Uses `FT_ATOMIC_STORE_PTR_RELEASE` (not bare assignment) for free-threaded safety.

### Concurrent-modification guard

`list_reverse_impl` uses `@critical_section` (Argument Clinic directive), which generates `Py_BEGIN_CRITICAL_SECTION(self)` / `Py_END_CRITICAL_SECTION()` in the wrapper. **No version-tag recheck; no `Py_BEGIN_ALLOW_THREADS`.**

### Argument Clinic template — `list.insert` lines 1171–1190

```
/*[clinic input]
@critical_section
list.insert

    index: Py_ssize_t
    object: object
    /

Insert object before index.
[clinic start generated code]*/
```

`@critical_section` on any list method that mutates in-place. `list.pop` (lines 1573–1587) shows `Py_ssize_t = default_value` syntax.

### `listmethods[]` — lines 3597–3615 (last entries before sentinel)

```c
    LIST_SORT_METHODDEF
    {"__class_getitem__", Py_GenericAlias, METH_O|METH_CLASS, ...},
    {NULL, NULL}   /* sentinel */
```
Insert `LIST_ROTATE_METHODDEF` after `LIST_SORT_METHODDEF`, before `__class_getitem__`.

### Complete stub (two pieces)

```c
/* Helper: reverse arr[lo..hi) in-place */
static void
_list_reverse_slice(PyObject **arr, Py_ssize_t lo, Py_ssize_t hi)
{
    --hi;
    while (lo < hi) {
        PyObject *t = arr[lo];
        FT_ATOMIC_STORE_PTR_RELEASE(arr[lo], arr[hi]);
        FT_ATOMIC_STORE_PTR_RELEASE(arr[hi], t);
        ++lo; --hi;
    }
}

/*[clinic input]
@critical_section
list.rotate

    n: Py_ssize_t = 1
    /

Rotate the list n steps to the right (negative n rotates left).
[clinic start generated code]*/

static PyObject *
list_rotate_impl(PyListObject *self, Py_ssize_t n)
/*[clinic end generated code: output=<hash> input=<hash>]*/
{
    Py_ssize_t len = Py_SIZE(self);
    if (len == 0 || len == 1)
        Py_RETURN_NONE;

    n %= len;
    if (n < 0)
        n += len;
    if (n == 0)
        Py_RETURN_NONE;

    /* Three-reversal rotation: rotate right by n */
    PyObject **items = self->ob_item;
    _list_reverse_slice(items, 0, len);   /* reverse whole list   */
    _list_reverse_slice(items, 0, n);     /* reverse first n      */
    _list_reverse_slice(items, n, len);   /* reverse remaining    */
    Py_RETURN_NONE;
}
```

