### Gotchas summary

| Area | Gotcha |
|------|--------|
| 1 | GC file is `Python/gc.c`, not `Modules/gcmodule.c`, in this CPython version |
| 2 | `dict_popitem` handles two entry struct types (Unicode vs general); `pop_last` must do the same |
| 2 | `DKIX_DUMMY` not `DKIX_EMPTY` — cannot revert a slot to EMPTY without rebuilding the probe chain |
| 3 | `frozenset_methods[]` is a separate array; `cartesian_product` needs an entry in both |
| 3 | Thread safety for two-set ops uses `Py_BEGIN_CRITICAL_SECTION2`, not the single variant |
| 4 | `type_getattro` is actually `_Py_type_getattro_stackref` in this version — different from `PyObject_GenericGetAttr` |
| 5 | `bytes.find` uses Clinic + METH_FASTCALL, **not** METH_VARARGS — new method must also use Clinic |
| 5 | `FASTSEARCH` returns one position per call; the loop must advance `start += pos + m` |
| 6 | Swaps must use `FT_ATOMIC_STORE_PTR_RELEASE`, not bare `=`, to match `reverse_slice` |
| 6 | `@critical_section` generates the lock wrapper automatically; don't add `Py_BEGIN_CRITICAL_SECTION` manually in `_impl` |

