### n=0 edge case
When n % len == 0, n becomes 0. The code then calls:
- _list_reverse_slice(arr, 0, 0): hi-- = -1 < lo=0, loop doesn't execute ✓
- _list_reverse_slice(arr, 0, len): full reverse
- _list_reverse_slice(arr, 0, len): full reverse again → back to original ✓
So n=0 (or n=len, n=-len, etc.) is correctly a no-op without any special case needed.

